msgctxt "sn35.79:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.79:0.2"
msgid "8. Gilānavagga "
msgstr "8. Sick "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 79. Paṭhamaavijjāpahānasutta → avijjāsuttaṃ (bj) | avijjā 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.79:0.3"
msgid "79. Paṭhamaavijjāpahānasutta "
msgstr "79. Giving Up Ignorance (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn35.79:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … "
msgstr "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn35.79:1.2"
msgid "ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.79:1.3"
msgid "“atthi nu kho, bhante, eko dhammo yassa pahānā bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, is there one thing such that by giving it up a mendicant gives up ignorance and gives rise to knowledge?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.79:2.1"
msgid "“Atthi kho, bhikkhu, eko dhammo yassa pahānā bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjatī”ti. "
msgstr "“There is, mendicant.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn35.79:3.1"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante, eko dhammo yassa pahānā bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjatī”ti? "
msgstr "“But what is that one thing?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.50, sc4
msgctxt "sn35.79:4.1"
msgid "“Avijjā kho, bhikkhu, eko dhammo yassa pahānā bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjatī”ti. "
msgstr "“Ignorance is one thing such that by giving it up a mendicant gives up ignorance and gives rise to knowledge.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn35.79:5.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃ pana, bhante, jānato, kathaṃ passato bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjatī”ti? "
msgstr "“But how does a mendicant know and see so as to give up ignorance and give rise to knowledge?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn35.79:6.1"
msgid "“Cakkhuṃ kho, bhikkhu, aniccato jānato passato bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjati. Rūpe … cakkhuviññāṇaṃ … cakkhusamphassaṃ … "
msgstr "“When a mendicant knows and sees the eye, sights, eye consciousness, and eye contact as impermanent, ignorance is given up and knowledge arises. "

msgctxt "sn35.79:6.2"
msgid "yampidaṃ, cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi aniccato jānato passato bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjati … pe … "
msgstr "And also knowing and seeing the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact as impermanent, ignorance is given up and knowledge arises. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.79:6.3"
msgid "manaṃ aniccato jānato passato bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjati. Dhamme … manoviññāṇaṃ … manosamphassaṃ … "
msgstr "Knowing and seeing the mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, and mind contact as impermanent, ignorance is given up and knowledge arises. "

msgctxt "sn35.79:6.4"
msgid "yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi aniccato jānato passato bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjati. "
msgstr "And also knowing and seeing the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact as impermanent, ignorance is given up and knowledge arises. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.79:6.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, jānato evaṃ passato bhikkhuno avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjatī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant knows and sees so as to give up ignorance and give rise to knowledge.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.79:6.6"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr ""

